I wish I had requested a refund when I could. Do NOT buy from this seller.

review.title: Great beginner stick
review.review: I've been using the drone for a few weeks now, all stock parts, on guilty gear strive. Before on PS5 game pad I had issues with inputting reversal supers or with timing dash macro, but now those actions feel a lot easier for me. It did take a bit to get used to the game again, but I'd say I'm at the same level as I was with a controller now. Also, I ordered from Amazon Warehouse and it said item case was damaged. The stick itself is perfect, but the blue qanba box(which was in a brown qanba box which was in a brown amazon box) was damaged. All in all great beginner buy!

review.review_data: Reviewed in the United States on June 10, 2021
review.title: WORKS ON PS5 WITH GAMES
review.review: I bought this just for GG Strive on PS5 since it was listed on Sony's site as being officially licensed. It works flawlessly with no set up. Simply plug it into your PS5 and it will work with PS5 & PS4 games. You can use it on any game but if the game uses twin analog stick for movements it wont work too well. I def recommend this as a starter arcade stick because its made of mostly plastic and already I'm kinda worried if I go too hard on it during a session I'll end up snapping off the joystick. If I end up using it a lot I will upgrade to a more sturdy (expensive) model.
product.title: Qanba Drone Joystick for PlayStation 4 and PlayStation 3 and PC (Fighting Stick) Officially Licensed Sony Product
